abstract = {{In the Kingman coalescent tree the length of order \$r\$ is defined as the sum of the lengths of all branches that support \$r\$ leaves. For \$r=1\$ these branches are external, while for \$r\textbackslashge2\$ they are internal and carry a subtree with \$r\$ leaves. In this paper we prove that for any \$s\textbackslashin\textbackslashmathbb\{N\}\$ the vector of rescaled lengths of orders \$1\textbackslashle r\textbackslashle s\$ converges to the multivariate standard normal distribution as the number of leaves of the Kingman coalescent tends to infinity. To this end we use a coupling argument which shows that for any \$r\textbackslashge2\$ the (internal) length of order \$r\$ behaves asymptotically in the same way as the length of order 1 (i.e., the external length).}}, 
